Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.79,0:00:04.61,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Currently, we lack information.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.10,0:00:08.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We should consider the possibility \Nthat it doesn't have a mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.53,0:00:11.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, we'll probably \Nhave to use brute force.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.79,0:00:14.40,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.40,0:00:16.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.77,0:00:23.00,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,In that case,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.93,0:00:28.50,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I may be able to kill Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.56,0:00:31.42,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.07,0:00:32.86,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.73,0:00:42.92,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.92,0:00:45.01,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's come up with a strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.11,0:00:58.03,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,You're there like the wind
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.03,0:01:02.66,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Closing your eyes at sunset
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.66,0:01:08.29,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's on your mind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.58,0:01:13.63,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(857,1)\blur0.25\fs35\fnGeorgia\fsp3.9\c&HFFFE65&\pos(328,254)\clip(109,253,547,294)\t(3943,4986,\clip(109,253,110,294))}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.01,0:01:17.01,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With your eyelids open
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.01,0:01:21.60,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Your eyes shone like glass
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.60,0:01:28.35,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,It faintly smelled like a sunny day
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.28,0:01:39.49,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Clear up the sky, let flowers bloom
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.49,0:01:43.70,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Bloom and blame it on the sunny sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.70,0:01:48.08,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the rain, when it stops
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.08,0:01:53.09,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Will make you shine in the sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.09,0:01:58.47,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Calm the stirring sounds in my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.47,0:02:02.51,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,We go like the sunny wind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.51,0:02:06.93,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Go on and fly over that cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.93,0:02:11.77,Songs_OP2,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Further and further away
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.98,0:02:17.99,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(387,269.5)}Episode 25: A Fatal Vulnerability
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.99,0:02:25.90,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,To confirm: if the replica has a mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.90,0:02:30.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,we'll use Edel's hypnosis magic \Nto penetrate my mental defenses,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.71,0:02:33.04,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,and Fern will kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.04,0:02:33.49,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.79,0:02:35.53,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,"Yes"?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.18,0:02:40.62,Default,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Dünste.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.75,0:02:50.20,Default,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Ms. Edel?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.38,0:02:55.87,Default,DÜNSTE,0000,0000,0000,,She dropped out when we were \Nattacked by Sense's replica.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.43,0:03:00.20,Default,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Mr. Blei as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.00,0:03:06.96,Default,DÜNSTE,0000,0000,0000,,I was able to escape because he kept it busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.88,0:03:11.05,Default,DÜNSTE,0000,0000,0000,,I hope he made it out safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.81,0:03:21.99,Default,BLEI,0000,0000,0000,,Leave me! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.65,0:03:27.90,Default,DÜNSTE,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.19,0:03:30.69,Default,BLEI,0000,0000,0000,,It's better than neither of us passing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.40,0:03:39.41,Default,DÜNSTE,0000,0000,0000,,I have information.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.86,0:03:41.59,Default,DÜNSTE,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we work together?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.95,0:03:46.32,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,That was my intention from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.94,0:03:50.25,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anyone who can treat this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.21,0:03:55.59,Default,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,I have a holy scripture. \NI can cast simple healing spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.08,0:03:57.07,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.22,0:04:05.31,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.79,0:04:08.30,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The replicas don't have minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.69,0:04:11.80,Default,DÜNSTE,0000,0000,0000,,No. According to Ms. Edel,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.80,0:04:15.30,Default,DÜNSTE,0000,0000,0000,,they merely imitate the \Nfunctions of a mind precisely
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.30,0:04:17.65,Default,DÜNSTE,0000,0000,0000,,without actually having one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.59,0:04:21.70,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there goes the easy way \Nof taking one down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.61,0:04:25.56,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to plan accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.24,0:04:31.58,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,But, Frieren, there's still \Ntoo much that we don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.28,0:04:37.85,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The biggest question is: what are those \Nreplicas, and who created them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.34,0:04:41.67,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,We can hardly take them on \Nwithout knowing their nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.39,0:04:45.29,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,In particular, we need to know whether \Nor not the replicas themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.29,0:04:46.97,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,have any unique weaknesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.43,0:04:52.39,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,If that replica really is as strong as you, \Nthen we'd likely suffer casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.45,0:04:56.71,Default,SENSE,0000,0000,0000,,I won't answer that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.71,0:04:57.88,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't think you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.51,0:05:00.89,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,They don't have any weaknesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.50,0:05:04.08,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,The replicas are being controlled
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.08,0:05:07.21,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,by a monster from the mythical era \Nknown as the Spiegel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.78,0:05:09.05,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Lawine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.05,0:05:10.79,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.10,0:05:15.06,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,My oldest brother was in the advance party \Nthat the Continental Magic Association
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.06,0:05:18.58,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,sent into the Tomb of the Ruined King.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.54,0:05:24.89,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,So you had information. \NNo wonder you made it this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.62,0:05:29.87,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,But you made an irrational choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.41,0:05:35.94,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,You should've shared your information \Nand worked with us from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.94,0:05:39.01,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't feel like we could've at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.42,0:05:43.32,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,And Frieren and Fern left before we knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.32,0:05:44.99,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, old man,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.99,0:05:48.48,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,you're the type to mercilessly abandon \Nyour allies unless there are rules against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.56,0:05:52.54,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone would think twice \Nabout working with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.84,0:05:55.99,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,She really doesn't like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.99,0:05:58.77,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that I'm old,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.77,0:06:01.80,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,but there's something that stings \Nabout having it said to my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.21,0:06:04.58,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you should apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.58,0:06:06.18,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.02,0:06:11.79,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,According to the advance party's \Nobservation report,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.79,0:06:17.16,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,the Spiegel is in the treasure room \Non the other side of that door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.80,0:06:22.10,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,The monster itself is weak \Nand has no way of attacking directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.30,0:06:26.61,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Once we defeat it, \Nall the replicas will disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.70,0:06:31.11,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,That matches what our mana detection revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.73,0:06:35.71,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The monster is on the other side of the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.71,0:06:39.90,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,but it's shut fast with a \Npowerful sealing spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.50,0:06:45.83,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I've confirmed that as well. \NMy replica must've done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.87,0:06:50.84,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a spell that shuts the door of a \Ntreasure vault at the risk of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.25,0:06:54.87,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Even among folk magic, \Nit's a top-class sealing spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.60,0:06:58.82,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That door won't open \Nuntil the caster is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.36,0:07:04.04,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We could ignore the door \Nand break through a wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.04,0:07:06.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but they've probably already \Naccounted for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.94,0:07:16.06,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, we'll have to defeat that replica \Nif we want to take down the Spiegel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.13,0:07:19.51,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,If we want to take it down, \Nthen we'd better hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.22,0:07:21.70,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.99,0:07:27.31,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,The Spiegel creates replicas \Nof everyone within the dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.86,0:07:33.46,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Over time, the replicas begin to gather \Nat the bottom of the dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.78,0:07:41.44,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Aside from my brother's unit, most members \Nof the advance party died...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.84,0:07:48.10,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,right here, just before the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.06,0:07:56.29,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.29,0:07:57.35,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.01,0:08:02.34,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The replicas precisely imitate the \Nfunctions of a mind, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.70,0:08:05.92,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, any vulnerabilities \Nin their behavioral patterns
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.92,0:08:07.84,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,would be the same as the original's, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.15,0:08:09.58,Default,DÜNSTE,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.51,0:08:14.96,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, we may have a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.37,0:08:17.68,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What vulnerability are you thinking of?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.04,0:08:25.79,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, could you go stand by that wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.19,0:08:26.73,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.45,0:08:47.73,Default,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,Was that…?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.32,0:08:52.16,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Incredible. I don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.16,0:08:53.86,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.81,0:08:56.48,Default,KANNE,0000,0000,0000,,Did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.48,0:08:57.43,Default,LAWINE,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.43,0:09:02.04,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,This is Frieren's fatal vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.04,0:09:05.51,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't I notice when I fought her?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.96,0:09:12.06,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,No, I couldn't notice because of my \Npreconceptions about experienced mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.84,0:09:19.32,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,When casting a spell, she stops \Ndetecting mana for a brief moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.71,0:09:23.43,Default,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that a common mistake \Nmade by apprentice mages?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.43,0:09:25.84,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I've never been very good about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.13,0:09:29.59,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,If you're aware of it, \Nthen why didn't you say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.01,0:09:32.17,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.17,0:09:34.47,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This is hardly the time to be saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.51,0:09:39.72,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,But she's far too skilled in all other areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.62,0:09:45.13,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imagine there are many mages \Nwho could exploit that vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.13,0:09:48.00,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, let's discuss our strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.76,0:10:13.58,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,Supposing we can handle Frieren's replica, \Nwhat about the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.58,0:10:15.63,DefaultTop,LAUFEN,0000,0000,0000,,Won't they all disappear \Nif we defeat the Spiegel?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.61,0:10:16.82,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, you seem to be having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.63,0:10:17.64,DefaultTop,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,The replicas will probably \Ngather before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.63,0:10:18.67,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.46,0:10:29.27,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like we've got a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.63,0:10:33.92,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Eisen will draw the enemy to him, \Nand I'll attack from the flank.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.08,0:10:37.17,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, you'll provide supporting fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.17,0:10:38.27,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What about Heiter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.27,0:10:40.68,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Today's an off day for him. He's hungover.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.29,0:10:43.65,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.50,0:11:06.56,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking about \Nall the times we discussed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.56,0:11:09.06,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,how we'd beat the dungeon boss like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.89,0:11:32.96,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.96,0:11:35.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's begin the attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.47,0:11:38.21,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Can we win?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.51,0:11:43.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. There isn't a dungeon \Nthat can't be conquered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.94,0:11:49.81,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the mage of the party that cleared \Nthe most dungeons in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.05,0:11:59.62,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you two sure you don't need any help \Nfighting Frieren's replica?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.10,0:12:04.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The fewer of us there are, the easier \Nit will be to predict its movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.83,0:12:12.46,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'd almost certainly win if we all fought, \Nbut most of us would probably die.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.40,0:12:16.93,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt we'd even have the time \Nto use our escape golems.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.46,0:12:23.75,Default,RICHTER,0000,0000,0000,,So slowing down the replicas gathering \Nat the bottom is more important.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.10,0:12:33.01,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,If they surround us, we're all dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.04,0:12:36.29,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Follow the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.29,0:12:39.02,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Got it. Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.23,0:12:43.58,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.55,0:13:04.54,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.66,0:13:09.77,Default,DENKEN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's discuss our weakest matchups.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.29,0:13:36.32,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Judradjim.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.37,0:13:44.30,DefaultItalics,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's behaving just like Ms. Frieren predicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.07,0:14:02.11,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Vollzanbel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.52,0:14:06.60,DefaultItalics,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I stopped detecting mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.06,0:14:10.82,DefaultItalics,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be wary of Fern, \Nwho used that opportunity to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.25,0:14:15.69,DefaultItalics,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll be busy dealing with \Nthe equally-matched opponent in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.60,0:14:19.49,DefaultItalics,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I won't have time to look for Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.83,0:14:25.91,DefaultItalics,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,After all, no one knows better than I do \Nhow frightening I can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.63,0:14:32.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:37.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Not even I can easily detect you \Nwhen you're completely hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.99,0:14:42.68,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure I should use \NZoltraak to attack, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.08,0:14:46.06,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the quickest spell there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.27,0:14:52.44,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, Zoltraak is a relatively \Nnew spell for elves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.75,0:14:57.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Not enough time has passed for us \Nto reflexively defend against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.02,0:15:03.45,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It takes only a moment \Nfor us to respond to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:06.96,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but the time we spend thinking \Nabout it causes a delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.63,0:15:09.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're different, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.67,0:15:15.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Zoltraak has existed since your birth. \NTo you, it's nothing special.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.57,0:15:19.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a fundamental mage spell \Nengraved into your being.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.98,0:15:25.36,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Your Zoltraak can kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.91,0:15:28.48,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Hit it with all the mana you've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.87,0:15:50.64,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, I thought you didn't like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.64,0:15:53.27,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Why have you come to see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.27,0:15:57.57,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I thought we'd never meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.71,0:16:01.64,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I came to deliver my master's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.44,0:16:05.34,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's been fifty years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.19,0:16:09.23,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So Flamme has died.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.64,0:16:12.09,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're not sad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.86,0:16:15.02,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I only trained her on a whim.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.47,0:16:23.47,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's practically a report.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.98,0:16:26.03,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What does it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.50,0:16:31.27,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,The emperor has authorized \Nmagical research nationwide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.68,0:16:37.92,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Until now, human societies have considered \Nmagic to be a technique used by demons,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.92,0:16:41.37,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,and openly studying it was forbidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.08,0:16:44.19,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Flamme encouraged him to allow it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.52,0:16:49.70,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,and had been training the newly \Nestablished imperial mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.04,0:16:55.07,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,She wants me to take over for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.95,0:16:59.26,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Such greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.33,0:17:06.55,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Receiving authorization to study magic \Nis a feat on its own, but she wants more.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.24,0:17:09.46,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that such an impressive achievement?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.07,0:17:14.47,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,The continent's largest united empire \Nis set to begin studying magic
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.47,0:17:16.84,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,and adopting it for military use.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.75,0:17:20.40,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,The neighboring nations are sure to respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.40,0:17:24.85,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,In just a few decades, magic will \Nspread throughout the continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.92,0:17:29.62,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,We'll enter an era in which \Nall of humanity can use magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.83,0:17:33.04,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,In the near future,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.04,0:17:36.93,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,humanity will acquire the strength to fight \Nback against the Demon King's forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.41,0:17:40.79,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That's incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.24,0:17:42.63,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.58,0:17:49.76,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.75,0:17:52.79,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Leave, Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.40,0:17:56.37,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I can't comply with this final request.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.37,0:17:58.00,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I find it truly displeasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.02,0:18:02.86,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,An era in which anyone can use magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.51,0:18:05.97,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Magic should be special.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.91,0:18:09.76,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I won't teach anyone who lacks talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.70,0:18:13.17,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,How dare she send this to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.17,0:18:16.16,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Flamme and I remained unable to understand \Neach other until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.05,0:18:20.22,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,She was only ever a student \NI trained on a whim.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.66,0:18:26.92,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,My master said you'd probably \Nget upset and tear up her will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.27,0:18:34.29,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But she wanted to tell you her dream \Nhad come true regardless.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.01,0:18:36.80,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't make sense, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.08,0:18:42.90,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm leaving now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.55,0:18:46.28,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt we'll meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.28,0:18:47.21,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.45,0:18:51.74,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Before you go, walk with me a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.18,0:18:55.70,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,After all, we have all the time in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.68,0:19:04.22,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,An era in which anyone could use magic \Nwas Flamme's dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.83,0:19:09.85,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt she cared about helping humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.85,0:19:15.20,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,or the strength to fight the \NDemon King's forces at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.31,0:19:23.26,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what her favorite spell was?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.28,0:19:26.29,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,A spell to create a field of flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.66,0:19:31.14,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,A useless, foolish spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.33,0:19:39.08,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,She truly loved magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.57,0:19:45.34,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,She genuinely wished for everyone in the \Nworld to be able to cast spells like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.88,0:19:48.77,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It disgusted me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.68,0:19:56.05,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,It was the fanciful dream of a girl, \Nbut it's what she really wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:20:04.11,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,She told me about this dream of hers \Nwhen she was a child much shorter than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.69,0:20:10.26,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I thought that era \Nwouldn't arrive for many more years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.26,0:20:13.44,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think she could accomplish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.74,0:20:22.00,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,To me, her life was so short \Nas to be practically nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.00,0:20:25.06,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,and yet she became the founder \Nof humanity's magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.76,0:20:29.14,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,My master was always quick to decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.64,0:20:32.36,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It felt like she was in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.42,0:20:36.86,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Humans have limited lifespans.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.86,0:20:39.64,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,They exist much closer to death than we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.16,0:20:46.69,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,We must all make important decisions \Nat several points in our lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.69,0:20:50.36,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,but humans cannot afford to delay them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.27,0:20:56.22,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,We can afford to wait a century or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.88,0:21:00.76,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Even ignoring them for a millennium \Nposes no obstacle,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.12,0:21:05.99,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,as our time is closer to an eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.35,0:21:13.28,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, many years have passed \Nsince humanity created
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.28,0:21:15.16,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,what could be called a civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.37,0:21:19.49,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, their progress \Nwill begin to accelerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.89,0:21:24.47,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,A mere thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.02,0:21:28.87,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,In a mere thousand years, \Nthe era of humans will arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.51,0:21:37.01,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,The humans will overtake us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.47,0:21:46.48,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,Do not neglect your training, Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.13,0:22:02.53,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,If anyone kills you, \Nit will be either the Demon King…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.13,0:22:07.14,Flashback,SERIE,0000,0000,0000,,or a human mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.86,0:22:14.56,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking forward to it, Serie.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.48,0:22:23.15,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to see so many \Ndifferent kinds of mages and spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.01,0:22:53.14,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm alright (I'll be alright)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.14,0:22:56.06,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I hear you (I care about you)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.06,0:23:01.65,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The wind teases this hair that's longer now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.65,0:23:04.07,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,There's meaning in everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.57,0:23:07.07,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the days that came to a halt
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.65,0:23:13.70,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I finally understand,\NI've caught up to you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.70,0:23:17.50,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,See, things that couldn't have been
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.50,0:23:20.37,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Seen if it weren't for these eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:25.05,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why? They begin to overflow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.05,0:23:31.30,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I won't ask to see you, so at least
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.30,0:23:37.06,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Let me remember the past, just for today
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.06,0:23:43.06,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we were to meet again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.06,0:23:48.94,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,No more hesitations, I'd choose the present
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.03,0:23:52.99,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime, anywhere, yah (wherever you are)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.99,0:23:57.62,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime, anywhere (smile for me)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.62,0:24:00.62,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be there (close your eyes,\Nand I'll always be there)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.62,0:24:03.38,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if there are no absolutes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.38,0:24:06.42,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm always aware of your thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.42,0:24:12.47,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Those tears will be alright,\Ndawn will surely break
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.93,0:24:19.39,Songs_ED2,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm whispering our lullaby\Nfor you to come back home
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.14,0:24:20.91,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's end this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.91,0:24:23.00,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Worst case, we could both die.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.54,0:24:25.93,DefaultOverlap,FERN/ID,0000,0000,0000,,Incredible, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.18,0:24:24.64,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.82,0:24:25.37,DefaultTop,FRIEREN/ID,0000,0000,0000,,This opening won't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.37,0:24:27.08,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We expected this much.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.19,0:24:27.73,DefaultOverlap,FRIEREN/ID,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to do it after all.
